The paper deals with the task of predicting saliency in videos using both audio and visual information. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques such as 3D CNNs for feature extraction and mapping also suggests a possible fit under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of eye tracking data, which could potentially fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper does not explicitly deal with software development or hardware implementation, ruling out the software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
